A woman who pleaded guilty to killing her husband was sentenced to one-day imprisonment. on March 9th 2021, high court judge Roselyne Aburili sitting in Siaya sentenced Truphena Ndonga Aswani to serve a non-custodial sentence of one day, that lasted the duration of the court session. This after confessing to murdering her husband James Oyengo on 14th December 2020. KTN news traced Truphena to a safe house in Webuye, where she has been living with her brother since she finished her one day sentence.